    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a high heat for 3 min until charred around the edges</p><p>Once charred, reduce the heat to low, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for a further 10-15 min until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix well</p><p>This is your <strong>chipotle dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your<strong> halloumi</strong> in half, then each half into 3 <strong>sticks per person</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Trim then finely slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the peppers are caramelised, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, the remaining <strong>red wine</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> and drained <strong>black beans</strong> and cook for a further 2 min until the beans have warmed through</p><p>Add the <strong>peppers</strong> and <strong>beans</strong> to the drained <strong>brown rice</strong> (reserve the pan for the next step!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Mexican rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wipe down the pan and return it to a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi sticks</strong></p><p>Cook on each side for 2 min until golden</p><p>Tip: alternatively cook on the BBQ until golden and slightly charred!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mexican-style-halloumi-with-black-beans/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>spring onion</strong> to the <strong>Mexican rice</strong> and mix well</p><p>Serve the <strong>halloumi sticks</strong> over the <strong>Mexican rice</strong> with the <strong>smoky dressing</strong> drizzled over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
